## The build

### Processes

The site is built with [Middleman](https://middleman.com "Check out the Middleman App site") – a static site generator written in Ruby. Moving to a static site was a big jump, but with my site having a small footprint and the customisation available, it was a no-brainer.

###<abbr title="Repository">Repo</abbr>

All of the code for this site is available [on Github](https://github.com/rbs-fueled/robsterlini "Check out robsterlini.co.uk on GitHub").

### Plugins

Various plugins are sampled or bastardised throughout the site, mainly to allow a jQuery-free site, but the only two that are injected unchanged are [Baseline.js](https://github.com/daneden/Baseline.js) and [OnScreen](https://github.com/jnb-fueled/onscreen).

